<br>
How do you handle newbies?  If they are polite?  If they are begging?  If they are demanding?  This means for anything. . . items, cash, ports, etc. . . .<br>
<br>
I personally will not talk to a begging or demanding newbie.  I just act like they are not there.  What I like to do when I'm bored and have a lot of useless stuff in the bank of on me, is go to G'fay and do a /who and see how many low level wizards there are.  Then I go hunt them down, and just start handing them things.  It makes me feel good, and they all seem to enjoy it too.<br>
<br>
Just curious to see how everyone handles them. . . <br>
<br>
P.S.  I don't even bother with the warrior type classes.  Probably not fair, but everytime I tried, I constantly found nothing but ones that were twinked to the max.  I think that sucks.  That to me really takes away from the game.  If you want to start an alt, why not start completely fresh and see what it's like to have to work your way up?  Sounds like more fun to me, but that doesn't mean anything. <p>Janden Furybringer
Lvl 28 Wizard
