<br>
/r I'm sorry, I don't speak English.<br>
<br>
For some reason, that always cracks me up.  I am a terrible person.<br>
<br>
But since any newbie can use it, I'm always sure to haste them if they're visible, and if they ask a question and it's obvious they're in dire need of help (as in they are completely clueless), I'll render aid.<br>
<br>
Beggars (pp and ph4t l3wtz beggars, and people who ask for the same buff more than twice- the first two times are free, after that they're trying to get me to be their free buffs station, and I have better things to do) get ignored.<br>
<br>
Anyone who demands anything of me gets ignored.<br>
<br>
Anyone who spams me with BS is put on my ignore list.<br>
<br>
Any newbie who does not fit in one of the above categories keeps to themselves, learning the game for themselves.  I always do run-by buffings of newbies of that sort as permitted by time, range, and mana (When bored or waiting for friends/guildies, I enjoy being a free buff station for newbies outside Felwithe. Until they start asking for Rune, and then I tend to laugh at the newbie in question before I throw a berserker strength on them). <p>del
