<br>
Few beggars are actually newbies.<br>
<br>
Newbies are the ones standing frozen in the middle of the newbie zone, while they frantically look things up in the manual (remember the manual), start hopping up and down for no reason (they're not actually talking, but are typing as they though were, and jump at each space between words) and race, naked save for their newbie tunic, at red conning critters.<br>
<br>
How do I treat newbies? Very well. I answer their questions, show them around town, and once in a while, I follow them around invisibly, and the ones really putting the effort in get some loot I was about to sell to a merchant, or a backpack filled with newbie gear (a 1hb staff, a senior apprentice robe, the good level 1-8 spells). <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long-2.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/29/01 4:27:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddalan.com/~berglund/ikp_hao.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: :/</span><hr size=1> How to tell a newbie from a beggar: <br>
